    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Style of Maya pottery painting in which figures and objects are drawn in black on a cream slip in a way suggesting their affiliation with contemporaneous, now lost, painted manuscripts; exemplified by a group of cylindrical vessels. The term is also used for wall paintings in this style.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
